Git CLI

------------------
Basic terminology:

Staged changes = Changes that have been marked to go into next commit snapshot
Unstaged changes = Changes you've made that Git has noticed but not yet marked to be included in next commit

------------

>>> REVIEWING STATUS AND HISTORY

To show state of repo: which branch you're on, staged and unstaged changes.
- git status

To see history of current branch and list of commits (q to quit)
- git log

Details of most recent commit
- git show
- git show <commit id>

To see all unstaged changes
- git diff

To see all staged changes
- git diff --staged

To see all changes from commit A to B:
- git diff <commit A> <commit B>


>>> STAGING AND UNSTAGING CHANGES

To stage all changes:
- git add .

To stage all changes for certain files:
- git add <filename(s)>

Unstage all changes:
- git reset
- git reset -p

Undo all unstaged changes (use with caution):
- git checkout .

>>> HANDLING COMMITS

Create commit with message:
- git commit -m "message to describe commit"

To edit most recent commit with staged changes:
- git commit --amend

To revert:
- git revert <commit id>

>>> BRANCHES

To create a branch:
- git branch <branch name>

To switch to a diff branch:
- git checkout <branch name>

>>> SYNCHRONIZING REMOTE AND LOCAL

Fetch changes for this brnach from remote to local (but don't apply these changes)
- git fetch

Fetch changes for this branch from remote to local, and update current local branch to match remote branch
- git pull

Push changes for this branch from local to remote
- git push
